  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>These are both solid mid-tier options that excel in different ways.</strong>
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> is the flexibility champion. Their ultra-high deductible options (up to $25K) are unique in the international insurance market and can save healthy expats significant money. Add in included US coverage, and IMG becomes the clear choice for Americans abroad or anyone who wants catastrophic-only protection at minimal cost.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>AXA Global</strong> is the stability champion. Backed by one of the world's largest insurers with €99 billion in revenue and EU Solvency II regulatory oversight, AXA offers peace of mind about long-term claim payment. Their European and Middle Eastern networks are genuinely strong, and the ability to exclude US coverage provides real savings for those who don't need it.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>The decision framework:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Need US coverage? → <strong>IMG</strong> (it's included)</li>
    <li>Want ultra-high deductibles? → <strong>IMG</strong> (only option)</li>
    <li>Based in Europe/Middle East? → <strong>AXA</strong> (stronger networks)</li>
    <li>Value regulatory backing? → <strong>AXA</strong> (EU Solvency II)</li>
    <li>Don't need US coverage? → <strong>AXA</strong> (exclude and save)</li>
  </ul>

