  <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Is IMG Global a legitimate insurer?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-2">Yes. IMG has operated since 1990 and insures hundreds of thousands of people globally. They're a legitimate mid-tier provider, not a fly-by-night operation. They're not as large as AXA, but they're established and financially stable.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Why doesn't AXA offer $10K+ deductibles?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-2">European insurers typically cap deductibles lower than American ones. AXA's €5,000 maximum reflects European market norms. If you want ultra-high deductibles, you'll need a US-based provider like IMG.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Is AXA's financial backing really that important?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-2">For most people, both providers are stable enough. AXA's size (€99B revenue) provides extra peace of mind for those who worry about insurers going bankrupt or not paying claims. IMG is smaller but has a solid track record. The difference matters more psychologically than practically for most expats.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Can I switch between these providers?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-2">Yes, but pre-existing conditions may face new waiting periods when switching. If you've developed health conditions during your coverage, switching can reset coverage for those conditions. Always compare carefully before switching.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Which processes claims faster?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-2">They're similar—both typically process claims in 7-14 business days. Neither is notably fast or slow. If claims speed is critical, neither of these is the answer; premium providers sometimes offer faster processing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Should I consider premium providers instead?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-2">Possibly, if you have specific needs. BUPA Global offers better mental health coverage. Cigna Global has excellent customer service. Aetna International provides CVS benefits. Premium providers cost 30-50% more but may be worth it for certain profiles. IMG and AXA are best for budget-conscious expats who don't need premium features.</p>
